Freethought
===========
Freethought is under the GNU license. 

Maybe people figured out how to see, hear and send images and sounds to a from brains and remote muscle movement back in the early 1800s, but at least now there is "FreeThought", a program, not quite as robust as GTK or QT, but still usable as a system to create a program with windows.


How to build:
make install
make debug_install (for debug library and examples)


Ubuntu notes:
sudo apt install libx11-dev libjpeg-dev libmp3lame-dev build-essential


MacOS notes:
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
brew install libjpeg
brew install lame
brew install gdb


Enjoy!
Ted Huntington



